*command
**
GSCR COMMAND

Form:           gscr [+] filename
Purpose:        Get screen contents from a Cifer 2632
Author:         MB (Ported to TRIPOS by RSC curtesy of DRM's TRIPOS cc)
Specification:

Reads text from the screen into the given file.
If the + flag is given, reads from entire 168 lines.


Examples:

Bugs:
        The page is usually scrolled by one line when the RETURN is pressed at
the end of the command line.
 
        As it is a C program ported from UNIX it dosen't know what RDARGS is.


